description:
Japanese title: Mezame no toki (目覚めの刻)

Throughout the village, Kitane’s fellow Guardian Shinobi with the Lightning Jutsu set up Limelight. With time running out for Hidden Leaf Village, Asuma continues desperately to try to stop Kitane and answers Kitane’s question, “Just what was the King anyway?” At that time, Naruto feels overwhelmed by Fouka’s mysterious jutsu. Will he be able to win with his Wind Chakra…? And what is this change that is occurring in Sora, who has been captured by Furido?
name: Moment of Awakening

description:
Japanese title: Zetsubō (絶望)

Naruto and Asuma catch up to Sora, only to find him shrouded in ominous chakra and undergoing a change. Naruto is shocked when Furido reveals the secret of Sora’s birth. Ten years earlier, remnants of the Nine Tails’ chakra that could not be sealed inside Naruto had been placed inside Sora. Imagining the suffering of one who shares the same fate as he, Naruto explodes with anger. This betrayal by one he trusted is the last straw for Sora, and he falls into despair.
name: Despair

description:
Japanese title: Kyōmei (共鳴)

Furido’s true form belongs to Kazuma, one of the Guardian Shinobi Twelve who had planned the coup d’état. Asuma puts his honor on the line and goes back ten years to battle Furido once more. Meanwhile, the rest of the Hidden Leaf ninja try to stop Sora who has begun to run rampant, but due to the intensity of the battle, one by one, their chakra runs out. Naruto summons all his strength to hold Sora back, but just then, the worst happens, something no one could have imagined.
name: Resonance

description:
Japanese title: Tomo yo (友よ)

Naruto desperately tries to suppress Nine Tails’ chakra and get through to Sora’s heart and soul. Naruto’s comrades are helpless against Sora’s powerful chakra and can only stand by and watch. Will Naruto’s attempts, at the risk of his life, be enough to stop Sora? Furido, satisfied that Sora is now on a rampage, tries to leave the battlefront. But he is confronted by Asuma, and the battle nears its end. The King, duty, father and son--this former Guardian Shinobi waged a heroic battle.
name: My Friend

description:
Japanese title: Shinobiyoru kyōi (忍び寄る脅威)

Work continues in Hidden Leaf Village to erase the scars of battle. As he watches Konohamaru and the others helping with the reconstruction, Iruka sees how his students have matured. Kakashi, who has returned from investigating the situation with Jiraiya, reports to Tsunade that the Akatsuki have begun to move. Tsunade worries about Naruto, whose training for a new jutsu has been interrupted.
name: The Quietly Approaching Threat

description:
Japanese title: Akatsuki shinkō (“暁”侵攻)

With Kakashi’s return, Naruto resumes training for his new jutsu. Kakashi explains that the transformation training will enter the next stage. This time, only Wind Chakra will be used to cut through a waterfall. Hidan and Kakuzu, who have captured Two Tails, leave it with Zetsu and head for the Land of Fire in search of Nine Tails. The first place they reach is the Fire Temple, where the priests go into a near panic, and Chiriku confronts the Akatsuki.
name: Akatsuki's Invasion

description:
Japanese title: Hoshizora no moto de (星空の下で)

The lone surviving priest is carried into Hidden Leaf Village where he reports the destruction of the Fire Temple. Upon learning of the Akatsuki’s infiltration into the Land of Fire, Tsunade orders the twenty newly formed teams into action. Meanwhile, Naruto trains hard to cut through a waterfall. As Sakura watches his harsh regimen, which would be impossible for a normal person, she realizes that training can no longer fill the gap between their power.
name: Under the Starry Sky

description:
Japanese title: Rōsō no inori (老僧の祈り)

In order to capture the Akatsuki, the Hidden Leaf cast a net that even an ant could not crawl through. Still, the Akatsuki elude them and frustrate Tsunade to no end. Around that time, Asuma and the others arrive at the Fire Temple, only to find it completely destroyed. Chiriku’s corpse is missing, and Asuma surmises that the Akatsuki were after the bounty on Chiriku’s head.
name: The Old Monk's Prayer

description:
Japanese title: Tsuginaru suteppu (次なる段階)

Naruto is learning the elements of Wind Style Jutsu, and Kakashi lectures him on the difficulties of developing a new jutsu. According to Kakashi even the Fourth Hokage was not able to embed elemental chakra into his jutsu. Naruto feels a heavy sense of responsibility and puts his entire being into developing the new jutsu. Meanwhile, the Akatsuki duo turns in Chiriku’s body to collect the bounty. What is the fate of the Hidden Leaf team who are pursuing them…?
name: The Next Step

description:
Japanese title: Bōgin (棒銀)

Asuma and his team finally confront Hidan, and a battle ensues. They fight with all their strength but are shocked at Hidan’s power. Kakuzu, the other Akatsuki member, also appears, and the Hidden Leaf seemed destined to lose. Escape is impossible, and Asuma grimly goes over a battle strategy… The strategy comes as a shock to everyone, especially Shikamaru.
name: Climbing Silver

description:
Japanese title: Kudasareta sabaki (下された裁き)

Hidan releases a baffling jutsu, and Asuma bears the brunt of the attack. The jutsu is a special trick which links Hidan with Asuma’s body. In that instant, Shikamaru uses his Shadow Strangle Jutsu to stop Hidan’s movements, but this jutsu does not last long. The battle rages on with little hope for reinforcements. Will Shikamaru be able to analyze Hidan’s jutsu and learn its secret in time…?
name: The Judgment

description:
Japanese title: Todokanu zekkyō (届かぬ絶叫)

Shikamaru unravels the secret of Hidan’s jutsu just in time, and Asuma attacks with all his being. However, even after his head is severed, Hidan continues to live. The Hidden Leaf, aghast at the sight of this undead man, are challenged by the other Akatsuki who has stood by in silence, Kakuzu. The Hidden Leaf team tries to rescue Asuma from the invincible Akatsuki duo, but Asuma falls victim to Hidan’s trick.
name: Unfulfilled Scream

description:
Japanese title: Saigo no kotoba (最期の言葉)

Asuma is mortally wounded by Hidan’s jutsu, and the Akatsuki have the rest of the Hidden Leaf in a bind. Just then, reinforcements arrive, led by Ino and Choji. They manage to come to the aid of their comrades, and once again, the Akatsuki find themselves confronted by the Hidden Leaf. But a mysterious figure suddenly interrupts them and the Akatsuki disappear. It seems they have barely avoided another battle, but Asuma’s wounds are deep and his end seems near.
name: Last Words

description:
Japanese title: Kanashiki shirase (悲しき報せ)

In a faraway land, the Akatsuki reveal their true aim of world conquest. And back at Hidden Leaf Village, Shikamaru gives his report of the mission to Tsunade. Tsunade worries about Kurenai’s reaction, but Shikamaru takes it upon himself to tell her the news of Asuma’s death. Meanwhile, Naruto is having difficulty with his new jutsu, but he gets a hint from Kakashi’s encouraging words. It is then that he receives the shocking news of Asuma’s death.
name: Sad News

first_appearance_objects.name: Demonic Statue of the Outer Path

object_credits.name: Demonic Statue of the Outer Path

description:
Japanese title: Daijuppan (第十班)

Asuma’s funeral is held in Hidden Leaf Village amid deep sadness. Shikamaru is the lone absentee, unable to get over the loss. Choji too is disconsolate. As each member of Team 10 deals with Asuma’s death, the question they ask themselves is “What must we do next?” Each comes to the same resolve--to stop and capture the Akatsuki. Tsunade adamantly opposes Team 10’s determination to set out on this mission. But an unexpected person offers to help.
name: Team Ten

description:
Japanese title: Tāgetto Rokkuon (標的捕捉)

Kakashi and Team 10 set out to stop the Akatsuki. Tsunade considers Naruto’s Team 7 to be the ideal back-up for Team 10 and orders Naruto to perfect his new jutsu within 24 hours. Meanwhile, Team 10 waits patiently for the battle against Kakuzu and Hidan. When Ino’s Mind Transfer Jutsu locates Hidan and Kukuzu, the gauntlet is thrown. Will Shikamaru’s strategy work in bringing down the Akatsuki duo?
name: Target: Locked On

first_appearance_objects.name: Demonic Statue of the Outer Path

object_credits.name: Demonic Statue of the Outer Path

description:
Japanese title: Kakuzu no nōryoku (角都の能力)

Shikamaru and Choji deliver the first blows in the battle, but they are thwarted by Kakuzu’s power. Kakashi counters Kakuzu’s trick and brings him down. But an unexpected phenomenon puts Shikamaru and the team in a danger. Meanwhile, Naruto is close to perfecting his new jutsu, and Yamato explains about the merits and relationship of the Change in Chakra Nature: the Five Elements.
name: Kakuzu's Abilities

description:
Japanese title: Osorubeki himitsu (恐るべき秘密)

Shikamaru and his comrades desperately counter the Fire Jutsu offensive. But continuously using his Rasengan and Lightning Blade takes its toll on Kakashi. Shikamaru decides that separating Hidan and Kakuzu is the only chance they have, and he sets out to create a diversion. Leaving Shikamaru to deal with Hidan, Kakashi takes on Kakuzu. But then, Kakuzu’s terrible secret is revealed…
name: Terrifying Secret

description:
Japanese title: Shikamaru no sai (シカマルの才)

Shikamaru battles Hidan alone, deep in the forest, and after depleting his chakra, sustains a deep wound. Hidan draws his blood as he lies near death. Around the same time, Kakashi also has been backed into a corner by Kakuzu’s relentless attack. Kakuzu is about to cut out Kakashi’s heart to replace his own, but a sudden change comes over him. All goes according to Shikamaru’s strategy, which gradually reveals itself…!
name: Shikamaru's Genius

description:
Japanese title: Hito o norowaba ana futatsu (人を呪わば穴二つ)

Naruto and Team Kakashi arrive just in time to assist Team Asuma. Sakura and Sai are ordered by Kakashi to aid Shikamaru, who is battling alone. Shikamaru knows that the moment of reckoning is near. How will Shikamaru stop the invincible Hidan? What does he have planned? And who will emerge victorious? Meanwhile, Naruto gathers data on Kakuzu by using his Shadow Clones, and he unleashes his perfected new jutsu, Wind Style: Rasen Shuriken.
name: When You Curse Someone, You Dig Your Own Grave

description: When the key witness in a homicide ends up dead while being held for questioning by the police, Gordon suspects that it's an inside job and looks to an old friend for information. Meanwhile, Oswald Cobblepot takes control of one of Fish Mooney's prized possessions, as she gets a gets a small taste of her own medicine.
name: Welcome Back, Jim Gordon

description:
Japanese title: Fūton: Rasenshuriken! (風遁·螺旋手裏剣!)

Ino and Choji are amazed at Naruto’s new jutsu, and Kakuzu senses the danger that it poses. But when released, the new jutsu dissipates before it reaches Kakuzu. Naruto’s comrades realize that the new jutsu will not bring Kakuzu down. But Naruto insists on another chance. His passionate plea moves his comrades, but Kakuzu changes to a long-distance attack in order to dodge Naruto. Will the Wind Style: Rasen Shuriken be able to reach him?
name: Wind Style: Rasen Shuriken!

description:
Japanese title: Chikara no daishō (力の代償)

Naruto’s uses his new jutsu to bring Kakuzu down. Tsunade welcomes the teams back home and orders Team Asuma and Team Yamato to take a break. Standing in front of Asuma’s grave, Shikamaru sees Kurenai, who is with child, and promises that he will protect the jewel that Asuma has left. Naruto’s right arm, which he injured during the battle, turns out to be quite serious. Realizing how dangerous the Wind Style: Rasen Shuriken is, Tsunade orders Yamato and Kakashi to never allow Naruto to use it again.
name: The Price of Power

description:
Japanese title: Shinobi no ketsui (忍の決意)

Just when peace has finally settled over the village word comes that Orochimaru’s hideout has been found. Tsunade orders Kakashi, Hinato, Shino, and Kiba on a search mission to find the hideout. Naruto is in a dilemma about his new jutsu, Wind Style: Rasen Shuriken, because of the damage the user sustains. Jiraiya returns to the village. Naruto seeks the guidance of his mentor, so Jiraiya and Naruto set out for the hot springs.
name: A Shinobi’s Determination

description:
Japanese title: Hakken — Orochimaru no ajito (発見 大蛇丸のアジト)

Naruto and Jiraiya arrive at the hot springs resort. As an alternative to the Wind Style: Rasen Shuriken, Jiraiya suggests to Naruto the collaboration ninjutsu with a ninja toad. But the toad summoned for Naruto’s partner turns out to be Mr. Gamariki, the ninja toad that didn’t get along with Naruto during his three-year training period. Meanwhile, upon receiving Orochimaru’s orders, Guren selects from her hideout a group of shinobi worthy of the mission.
name: Orochimaru’s Hideout Discovered

description:
Japanese title: Deai (遭遇)

Inside Orochimaru’s hideout Guren witnesses Sasuke defeating a thousand opponents. Having lost the opportunity to be Orochimaru’s new vessel in the past, Guren openly express her jealousy toward Sasuke. Seeing through Guren’s emotional state, Orochimaru proposes a plan. Meanwhile, Kabuto and Yukimaru conduct their experiment to summon the Three-Tailed Beast. Drained from the experiment, Yukimaru is taken by Kabuto to a nearby hot spring to heal.
name: Encounter

description:
Japanese title: Kayoiau kokoro (通い合う心)

Believing Naruto’s new jutsu is almost completed, Jiraiya heads off to investigate new information on the Akatsuki’s movements. His arm now healed, Naruto returns to the village to continue his training. At the Leaf Village Tsunade receives Kakashi’s message and begins her investigation into the mysterious crystal that was delivered.
name: Connecting Hearts

description: Jon impresses Tyrion at Castle Black; Ned confronts his past and future at King's Landing.
name: Lord Snow

description: Eddard investigates Jon Arryn's murder. Jon befriends Samwell Tarly, a coward who has come to join the Night's Watch.
name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things

description: Catelyn has captured Tyrion and plans to bring him to her sister, Lysa Arryn, at The Vale, to be tried for his, supposed, crimes against Bran. Robert plans to have Daenerys killed, but Eddard refuses to be a part of it and quits.
name: The Wolf and the Lion

description:
Japanese title: Kakusareta Shinjitsu (隠された真実)

The Elrics discover the horrific ingredient needed to create a Philosopher’s Stone. When night falls, they prowl the grounds of a secret laboratory in search of more facts - but the brothers find only danger.
name: Hidden Truths

description:
Japanese title: Daigo Kenkyūsho (第五研究所)

Ed and Al furiously battle the Fifth Laboratory’s psychotic guards. In the chaos, the truth behind the Philosopher’s Stone is buried beneath rubble - and disturbing new questions are unearthed.
name: The Fifth Laboratory

description:
Japanese title: Tsukurareta Omoi (創られた想い)

Al is haunted by the notion his entire existence was simply created by his brother. When the youngest Elric angrily reveals these suspicions, only Winry can convince him just how wrong he is about Ed.
name: Created Feelings

description:
Japanese title: Sorezore no Yukusaki (それぞれの行く先)

When the conspiracy surrounding the Philosopher’s Stone closes in on the highest ranks of the military, one of Mustang’s most trusted and cherished allies is murdered.
name: Separate Destinations

deck: Flash faces off against Pied Piper.
description: Dr Wells (Tom Cavanagh) receives a blast from the past when a former protege (Andy Mientus) returns to town for revenge.
name: The Sound and the Fury

has_staff_review.name: The Flash Episode #111 - "The Sound and the Fury"

deck: The one team member they’ve finally learned to trust, now has a devastating secret.
description:
The episode opens in 1983. A man named Gordon is being observed due to his powers (likely induced via experimentation). He has no eyes and teleports about an empty room wildly. He is comforted by a woman who has been observing him, possibly one of the experimenters, and possibly Skye's mother.

In the present day, HYDRA is reeling from their recent defeat, and Coulson seizes the initiative to strike hard.

Jemma Simmons sees a grotesquely transformed Raina crawling from the remnants of the alien city.
name: Aftershocks

description:
Arsenal (Colton Haynes) and Diggle (David Ramsey) confront Laurel (Katie Cassidy) about trying to step into her sister’s shoes and warn her to stop before she gets herself killed. However, when Brick (guest star Vinnie Jones) kidnaps the city’s Aldermen and threatens to kill them all unless the police evacuate The Glades, it’s all suits on deck.

Meanwhile, Ray (Brandon Routh) steps in to help Lance (Paul Blackthorne) and the police force fight Brick, showing Felicity (Emily Bett Rickards) a new side of her boss. Malcom (John Barrowman) tells Thea (Willa Holland) that Ra’s al Ghul (Matt Nable) is after him and his family and they must leave town immediately.
name: Midnight City

first_appearance_objects.name: Iron Man Stealth Armor Mk. I

object_credits.name: Iron Man Stealth Armor Mk. I

description:
Japanese title: Rasshu Barē no Kiseki (ラッシュバレーの奇跡)

The Elrics, realizing alchemy has yet to unlock the mysteries of creating life, feel powerless when a new friend goes into labor. Winry, however, jumps into action with a young thief named Paninya.
name: Miracle at Rush Valley

description:
Japanese title: Ichi wa Zen, Zen wa Ichi (一は全、全は一)

While visiting Izumi, their childhood teacher, the Elrics recall the early difficulties of grasping equivalent exchange. They also discover she shares their intimate knowledge of alchemy’s greatest taboo.
name: One is All, All is One

description:
Japanese title: Daburisu no Kemono-tachi (ダブリスの獣たち)

Al is abducted by chimeras led by the seemingly indestructible Homunculus known as Greed. When Ed’s rescue attempt falls short, Izumi proves once more that she’s got the brothers’ best interests in mind.
name: Beasts of Dublith
YatterWan and YatterPelican: Friends to the End

description:
Japanese title: Chika ni Hisomu Mono-tachi (地下にひそむ者たち)

In a violent clash with Greed, King Bradley proves to be a brutal opponent. But the man who finally destroys the Ultimate Shield is more powerful than even the Fuhrer himself.
name: Those Who Lurk Underground

description:
Japanese title: Tōhō no Shisha (東方の使者)

The Elrics scuffle with Ling Yao and his attendants, Lan Fan and Fu, visitors from Xing seeking the Philosopher’s Stone. Ed may not like him, but Ling Yao’s not leaving until he gets what he wants.
name: Envoy From the East

description:
Japanese title: Tomo no Ashiato (戦友の足跡)

After learning of Hughes’s fate, Ed and Al are ravaged by sadness and guilt. Envy still hides in plain sight among the State Alchemists, and another Homunculus is on the verge of infiltrating their ranks as well.
name: Footsteps of a Comrade-in-Arms

description:
Japanese title: Reitetsu na Honō (冷徹な焔)

Freed by an unlikely liberator, Ross’s escape is interrupted by Mustang. Even those most loyal to the Flame Alchemist are shaken by the controversial action he takes against the accused killer of Maes Hughes.
name: Cold Flame

description:
Japanese title: Chiisa na Ningen no Gōman na Tenohira (小さな人間の傲慢な掌)

Ed’s journey to a distant land of legend offers surprising new details behind Mustang’s alleyway encounter with Ross. After a fateful encounter of his own, Elric learns a stunning secret about Winry’s parents.
name: The Arrogant Palm of a Small Human

description:
Japanese title: Shinazaru Mono no Shi (死なざる者の死)

Mustang, Alphonse, Havoc, and Hawkeye split up to search a military laboratory. If Lust has her way, none of them will ever see each other alive again.
name: Death of the Undying

description:
Japanese title: Bozen no Chichi (墓前の父)

Hohenheim’s visit ends with a grave warning to Pinako, but Ed finds hope among the charred ruins of his childhood. Now more than ever, he has confidence that Al can be returned to his body.
name: Father Before the Grave

description:
Japanese title: Gusha no Zenshin (愚者の前進)

Hoping to learn more about the Homunculi, Ed and Al devise a risky strategy to lure the creatures out of hiding. Step one of the brothers’ plan: risk death at the hands of their most dangerous enemy - Scar.
name: Advance of the Fool

description:
Japanese title: Tōku no Senaka (遠くの背中)

Scar’s mission to destroy those who slaughtered his people is fueled by justifiable rage. Upon learning the role Scar played in her parents’ deaths, Winry claims those murderous feelings as her own.
name: Backs in the Distance

description:
Japanese title: Ikusaba no Shōjo (戦場の少女)

Cooperation between Mustang’s cabal and Ling Yao’s band leads to the capture of a Homunculus. Unfortunately, their actions also capture the eye of the Homunculus hiding atop the military’s ranks.
name: Girl On the Battlefield

description:
Japanese title: Hara no Naka (腹の中)

Gluttony’s twisted powers overwhelm the Elrics - and the creature’s appetite is satisfied by battle’s end. Meanwhile, Mustang acts on his suspicions of Bradley and finds himself in the belly of the beast.
name: Inside the Belly

description:
Japanese title: Yami no Tobira (闇の扉)

The Homunculi are winning. Ed and Ling face a horrific enemy within the hellish expanse of Gluttony’s gut. In Central, Mustang can only watch as his loyal band of soldiers is divided by Bradley.
name: Doorway of Darkness
Alumni Reunion in the Tatsunokon Kingdom

first_appearance_objects.name: Iron Man Stealth Armor Mk. I

object_credits.name: Iron Man Stealth Armor Mk. I

first_appearance_objects.name: Iron Man Stealth Armor Mk. I

object_credits.name: Iron Man Stealth Armor Mk. I

first_appearance_objects.name: Iron Man Stealth Armor Mk. I

object_credits.name: Iron Man Stealth Armor Mk. I

first_appearance_objects.name: Iron Man Stealth Armor Mk. I

object_credits.name: Iron Man Stealth Armor Mk. I

description: MALCOLM MAKES AN OFFER TO HELP TEAM ARROW — Still operating without Oliver (Stephen Amell) and desperate to stop Brick (guest star Vinnie Jones), Team Arrow is forced to consider Malcolm’s (John Barrowman) offer to help shut Brick down as Malcolm has a personal score to settle with the felon. Roy (Colton Haynes) and Laurel (Katie Cassidy) point out that the team could use some help to save the innocents of The Glades, but Felicity (Emily Bett Rickards) is adamantly against it. They look to Diggle to make the final decision. Meanwhile, the flashbacks chronicle Malcolm’s descent from kind-hearted father and husband to cold-blooded killer after the murder of his wife.
name: Uprising

description:
Japanese title: Saikai (再会)

Truths are exposed when Al finds the one called Father, and Mustang hears the tale of Bradley’s creation - but the most amazing revelation is reserved for Ed after he once again breaks alchemy’s greatest taboo.
name: Reunion

description:
Japanese title: Hazama no Utage (狭間の宴)

Visions of the past play out by a warming fire as Hohenheim reflects on the unavoidable follies of man: the pain that comes with a loving family; the hidden truths of alchemy; and the roots and results of war.
name: Interlude Party

description:
Japanese title: Otō-sama (おとうさま)

The Elrics come face to face with Father - and his face is familiar indeed. Powerless and amazed, Ed and Al can only watch as Father creates a new Homunculus with alchemy that should be impossible.
name: Father

description:
Japanese title: Gusha no Agaki (愚者の足掻き)

The Elrics are at Bradley’s mercy; if the brothers make one wrong move, those dearest to them will pay. As Mustang quietly gathers allies at his side, Ed discovers there may be no need to find a Philosopher’s Stone.
name: Struggle of the Fool

description:
Japanese title: Ishuvāru Senmetsusen (イシュヴァール殲滅戦)

As Edward hears Hawkeye’s tale of a time when idealistic young soldiers were tasked with genocide, the horrors of the Ishvalan battlefield are revealed.
name: The Ishvalan War of Extermination

description:
Japanese title: Gohyaku Nijū Senzu no Yakusoku (520センズの約束)

Even as his subordinates are scattered, Mustang finds he still has allies - unfortunately, so do his enemies. The Homunculi unleash one of the Ishvalan War’s most notorious killers to deal with Scar and Marcoh.
name: The 520 Cens Promise

description:
Japanese title: Daisōtō no Musuko (大総統の息子)

A secret encounter allows Mustang to spark new ambition in an old friend - an ally with loyal troops at his command. Meanwhile, Ed and Al share a chance meeting with their biggest fan - young Selim Bradley.
name: The Fuhrer's Son

description:
Japanese title: Burigguzu no Hokuheki (ブリッグズの北壁)

The frigid northern borderlands become a battlefield when Kimblee finally closes in on Scar. Deeper into the frozen wasteland, Ed and Al’s fight is against the bitter elements as they struggle to reach Fort Briggs.
name: The Northern Wall of Briggs
